It's time to destroy our bedroom. The last room in the house, where apart from a bit of decorating, nothing has been done yet.
The terrible electric fireplace and the hearth must go. We need to surround the chimney, replace the cracked mortar, and smooth it out. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch...
The dirty part of the work is done.
In the back of the chimney, we found a few dead birds, very dried out :(.
Everything is ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche has turned out well
A new closet will fit here (but we haven't even started on the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought to install this nice little vent flap so that the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the covering and cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there 🪺
The plasterer is done. The floor will be moved tomorrow!
The cork underlayer is in place, I've made a toilet paper roll dust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Parts for the floor are ready and can be moved. We're taking a tea break right now
Buhu. Today is going slowly because of super complicated cuts around the doorposts so we have a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be replaced). @user45@twitter.com has blessed me
Done, but at last! The crown was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Still missing are the floor in the hallway and all the skirting boards. The decorator will come in a month, so we currently have raw plaster look.
A bit more handywork in the evening to cut or carve the lower sections around the door frames where the floor should fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlayer is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then out at 5 AM to pick up item 1 in Heathrow, then a nap and a final rush in the hallway, the strips are fitted. Joints will be made when the glue is dry.
